oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Mack Vickery Studio Demos - 1967-12-07 Reel #1
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: The recording is of Mack Vickery (musician). The recording features a studio recording of: "Her Memory Starts Touching My Mind," and "Two Old Freight Trains" The recordings were created at the Columbia Recording Studios, in Nashville, Tennessee, for Boone Records. The recording is of the unedited studio session and labeled reel number one of two. The recording takes place on December 07, 1967.
